{[%evp 0,136,19,38,30,40,43,30,26,26,22,19,16,12,27,-7,-9,3,3,15,4,4,4,0,5,0,
46,16,59,-28,-35,-33,-15,-23,-30,-4,-12,-27,-26,-22,-21,-30,-34,-28,-15,-26,
-30,-29,-22,-17,-20,-36,-31,-36,-13,-31,-27,-49,-35,-40,-34,-33,-20,-23,-31,
-25,-22,-44,-48,-52,-59,-71,-74,-85,-90,-88,-80,-97,-91,-92,-91,-84,-79,-74,
-83,-77,-79,-83,-75,-79,-76,-75,-65,-92,-75,-65,-48,-46,-24,-38,-37,-44,-33,
-37,-35,-43,-44,-44,-37,-43,-46,-47,-43,-43,-50,-53,-53,-53,-58,-123,-138,-138,
-138,-161,-160,-140,-136,-146,-133,-133,-214,-287,-263,-473,-497,-507,-517,
-527,-557]} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 Bd6 {As we discussed in the
introduction, the drawback of this move order is that White can continue with
5.c4} 5. c4 Nf6 6. Nc3 (6. c5 {This system was discussed in some high-level
games, but I believe that Black should be fine after:} Be7 7. Bd3 b6 8. cxb6 (
8. Be3 {deserves attention}) 8... axb6 9. O-O O-O) 6... O-O 7. cxd5 {We are
familiar with this kind of pawn sacrifices. If Black manages to win the pawn
back then he should have an advantage.} (7. c5 {is possible here too, but
gives Black additional options} Re8+ 8. Be2 Bf8 {Of course Black can continue
with 8...Be7 as well, but this looks satisfactory}) 7... Nbd7 8. Be2 Nb6 9. Bg5
h6 10. Bxf6 (10. Bh4 Be7 11. O-O Nfxd5 $11) 10... Qxf6 {Now White will keep
the extra pawn for a time being, but Black has great compensation: bishop pair
and very active pieces.} 11. O-O Re8 12. Re1 Bg4 13. Ne5 Bf5 (13... Bxe2 14.
Qxe2 Qg5 {[%cal Rf7f6,Ra8d8]}) 14. Bf3 (14. f4 $1 $14) 14... Bxe5 15. dxe5 Rxe5
16. Rxe5 Qxe5 {Let's say that Black is on the better side of an equal position
because the d5-pawn will be a weakness in the future.} 17. Qe2 Qxe2 18. Bxe2
Re8 19. Rd1 $6 Na4 $1 20. Bb5 Nxc3 21. bxc3 Rd8 22. Be2 Kf8 {now Black's
position is much preferable. His king is more active and White has three pawn
islands. Wesley So converts his advantage at the end after some adventures.}
23. f3 Ke7 24. Kf2 Kd6 25. Rd4 a5 26. h4 Rd7 27. Bc4 Bc2 28. Ke3 Kc5 29. Kd2
Bg6 30. Bb3 f6 31. Ra4 Kb6 32. c4 Re7 33. c5+ Kxc5 34. Rxa5+ Kd6 35. Ra7 b6 36.
a4 Bf7 37. a5 bxa5 38. Ra6+ Kc5 39. d6 cxd6 40. Bxf7 Rxf7 41. Rxa5+ Kd4 42.
Ra4+ Kd5 43. Ra5+ Ke6 44. Ke3 Rb7 45. h5 d5 46. Kf4 Rb4+ 47. Ke3 Ke5 48. f4+
Ke6 49. Ra7 Kf5 50. Rxg7 Re4+ 51. Kd3 Rxf4 52. Rg6 Rg4 53. Rxh6 Rxg2 54. Rh8
Rh2 55. Kd4 Ke6 56. h6 Rh4+ 57. Ke3 d4+ 58. Kd3 Kf7 59. h7 Kg7 60. Rg8+ Kxh7
61. Rg1 f5 62. Kc4 Kh6 63. Kd5 Re4 64. Rg2 Kh5 65. Rg1 Kh4 66. Rg8 d3 67. Rg1
