1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. exd5 exd5 4. Nf3 Nc6 5. Bd3 Bd6 6. h3 (6. O-O Bg4 {
The most principled reaction} 7. Re1+ Nge7 8. h3 $2 (8. c3 $1 {was mandatory}
Qd7 {[%cal Rh7h5]}) 8... Bxf3 9. Qxf3 Nxd4 10. Qg4 Ne6 11. Nc3 c6 $17 {White
has no compensation for the sacrificed pawn. 0-1 (23) Koelle,T (2340)-Xiong,J 
(2709) Chess.com INT 2021}) 6... Nge7 7. O-O Nb4 8. Bb5+ $6 {this wasn't
necessary} c6 9. Be2 Bf5 10. Na3 a5 $1 11. c3 Na6 12. Nc2 Nc7 13. Ne3 Be4 14.
Ng5 Bg6 15. f4 {this is too optimistic} h6 16. f5 hxg5 17. fxg6 Nxg6 18. Nf5
Ne6 19. Nxd6+ Qxd6 20. Bg4 {White sacrifices a pawn for a bishop pair, but
objectively speaking Black's position is better and the compensation is not
enough} Ngf4 21. Qf3 O-O 22. Bf5 g6 23. Bc2 f5 24. Bd2 Nh5 $1 {The knight is
heading to "e4"} 25. Rae1 Nf6 26. Rxe6 $6 {panic} Qxe6 27. Bxg5 Rae8 28. Bd3
Ne4 $19 {Parham has no problem to convert his big advantage} 29. Bf4 Qf6 30.
Rd1 Qh4 31. a4 Re6 32. Be5 Ng5 33. Qf2 Qxf2+ 34. Kxf2 Nf7 35. Bc7 Nd6 36. Ra1
Ra8 37. Kf3 Kf7 38. b4 axb4 39. cxb4 Ke7 40. a5 Kd7 41. Bb6 Rae8 42. Kf4 Re3
43. Rd1 Nc4 44. Bxc4 dxc4 45. Rc1 c3 46. d5 R8e4+ 47. Kg5 Rg3+ 48. Kf6 Rxb4 49.
dxc6+ Kxc6 50. Bf2 Rd3 51. Kxg6 Rb2 52. Be1 Rxg2+ 53. Kxf5 c2 0-1

