18. Nd2 $14 {White has an advantage, but the game remains complicated} Nf4 19.
Qf3 g5 20. Bb4 Nc4 $1 {very nice pawn sacrifice} 21. Nxc4 dxc4 22. Qxb7 Qd5 23.
Qxd5+ Nxd5 {The computer is optimistic about White's chances, but I prefer
Black in this position. The knight dominates the bishop.} 24. Kf1 Kf7 25. Rxe8
Rxe8 26. Re1 Rd8 27. Rb1 Re8 28. g3 h5 29. Re1 Rd8 30. Re4 c6 31. bxc6 Rc8 32.
h4 g4 33. Re2 Rxc6 34. a5 a6 35. Rb2 Rc7 36. Bd6 Rd7 37. Bc5 Nxc3 38. Rc2 $2 (
