1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5 Ne7 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 c5 7. Nf3 {This
doesn't have individual value. White would either go h4 or a4 after this,
which would transpose into the other chapters.} h6 $1 8. h4 (8. Bd3 b6 $1 {
Typical reaction with the idea of exchanging the bishop with Ba6} 9. O-O Ba6
10. Nh4 Bxd3 11. Qxd3 cxd4 $1 (11... Nbc6) 12. cxd4 Qc7 13. f4 Qc4 $10) (8. a4
Qc7 $1 {Transposes}) 8... b6 9. Bb5+ Bd7 10. Bd3 c4 11. Be2 Ba4 {Another
important move which was only possible since White didn't play a4} 12. h5 Kd7
$1 13. Bf4 (13. Nh4 Kc6 {King is heading towards b7} 14. f4 Kb7 15. g4 $5 g6 {
Black is more than okay here.}) 13... Kc6 14. Nh2 Kb7 15. Ng4 Qd7 $132 *

