13,17,-41,-18,-17,-8,-61,-69,-89,-64,-108,-29,-144,-137,-223,-96,-281,-312,
-104,0,0,0,29994,29997,29998,29999,-30000]} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Bb4 4. e5
c5 5. a3 Bxc3+ 6. bxc3 Qc7 7. Nf3 Ne7 8. a4 h6 9. Bd3 b6 10. O-O Ba6 11. Bxa6
Nxa6 12. Qd3 Nb8 13. Nh4 Nbc6 14. f4 O-O 15. Ba3 Na5 16. Rae1 Qc6 17. g4 Qxa4
18. Bc1 cxd4 19. f5 Rac8 20. Bxh6 $3 {A devastating blow! Such vicious attacks
often occur in the French Defence, when Black castles kingside.} gxh6 ({
Black had no time for his planned action - taking on c3 with the rook, as after
} 20... Rxc3 21. Qd2 {White's attack is unstoppable, for instance:} Qxc2 (21...
gxh6 22. Qxh6 Qxc2 23. Qg5+ Kh8 24. Qxe7 $18) (21... exf5 22. Qg5 Ng6 23. Bxg7
Rfc8 24. Qh6 Qe8 25. gxf5 $18) 22. Qg5 Ng6 23. fxg6 $18) 21. f6 Nec6 22. Qd2 $1
{The queen is coming in with deceisive attack.} Kh7 (22... d3 {Petursson} 23.
h3 $18 {This does not change anything}) 23. Rf5 $1 {Another nice motif which
is quite recurring in these types of positions.} dxc3 (23... exf5 24. Nxf5 {
[%cal Rd2h6]} Kg8 25. Qxh6 {[%cal Rh6g7,Rf5g7] with unstoppable mate.}) 24.
Qxh6+ $1 Kxh6 25. Rh5# *

