{[%evp 0,17,22,22,22,33,33,6,6,-6,-6,-2,-19,-19,6,6,6,6,6,6]} 1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5
3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bd7 6. Be2 f6 {This is a very common way of playing.
Black immediately seeks to undermine the center.} 7. O-O (7. exf6 {does not
pose a challenge} Nxf6 8. O-O Bd6 {[%cal Ge6e5] Black finishes his development
and has no problems.}) 7... fxe5 {According to the database, this position has
been played almost 1000 times. Here, White is faced with an important decision:
whether to keep the Nf3 on board or not. In any case, the resulting structure
is the same.} 8. Nxe5 (8. dxe5 {is the less popular option}) 8... Nxe5 9. dxe5
*

