3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bd7 6. Be2 f6 7. O-O fxe5 8. Nxe5 Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qc7
10. c4 d4 {Pushing the pawn is a very commital decision and Black needs to
have figured out the position specifics before doing so!} ({In case of} 10...
Qxe5 11. Bh5+ g6 12. Bf3 {[%cal Gf1e1]} d4 13. Bxb7 Rb8 $11 {[%cal Ge5c7,Gf8d6]
White has enough compensation but Black is far from losing too}) 11. Re1 O-O-O
12. Bd3 Ne7 13. Nd2 Nc6 {Exercise: How to continue with White?} 14. Ne4 $1 {
