1. e4 e6 2. d4 d5 3. e5 c5 4. c3 Nc6 5. Nf3 Bd7 6. Be2 f6 7. O-O fxe5 8. Nxe5
Nxe5 9. dxe5 Qc7 10. Bf4 O-O-O $6 {Black always needs to be careful when to
castle! If he does it too early (without having completed his development), he
might rapidly come under attack} (10... Nh6 {[%cal Ge2h5] does not work here:}
11. c4 d4 12. Bxh6 gxh6 13. Bh5+ {[%csl Bf8][%cal Bf2f4,Bb1d2]}) (10... Ne7 {
[%cal Gg7g6,Gf8g7,Ge7g6] is the way Black should continue. Then, he has 2
setups at his disposal: one with Ng6 and one with g6, Bg7}) 11. a4 $1 {[%cal
Gb1a3,Ga3b5] Great move by Eljanov, going for the opponent's king without
further ado! White wants to go Na3, Nb5 and possibly sacrifice the knight to
open lines} (11. b4 {also deserves attention}) (11. c4 {does not promise White
much} d4 12. Nd2 Bc6 {Not allowing Ne4} (12... Ne7 $6 13. Ne4) 13. Bd3 g5 $1
14. Bxg5 Qg7 {[%cal Gg7g3]}) 11... Ne7 12. Na3 a6 13. Nb5 (13. b4 c4 14. Nc2 {
[%cal Gc2d4]} Ng6 15. Bg3 Nxe5 16. f4 $1 Nf7 17. f5 Bd6 18. fxe6 Bxe6 19. Nd4
$18) 13... axb5 14. axb5 {[%cal Ga1a8]} Qb6 (14... Be8 15. c4 $1 d4 16. Bf3 $18
) 15. c4 {[%cal Gf4d2,Gd2a5] Opening the diagonal for the dark-squared bishop
is lethal: Black has no good reaction} dxc4 16. Ra8+ Kc7 17. Qd6+ $1 Qxd6 18.
exd6+ Kb6 19. Rxd8 $18 {1-0 Black resigns.} 1-0

