[%cal Gd8g8,Gd7e8,Gh6f5] with the idea of ... Rdg8, the White queen is in huge
trouble.}) 15. Ndf3 $1 {Black is now forced to push his pawns and allow the
kingside to be locked} g4 16. Ng5 Nh6 17. h4 $1 gxh3 18. Nxh3 Rdg8 19. Qxh5 $2
(19. Bf3 {[%cal Ge1g2]} Nf5) 19... Nf5 20. Qe2 Bxa3 21. Ra1 Nb3 22. Rxa3 Nxc1
23. Qd2 Nb3 24. Qf4 Be8 25. Nc2 a6 26. Ng5 Qd8 27. Nf3 Qe7 28. Nb4 Bd7 $17 {
and Black is much better. After many mutual mistakes, the game ended in a draw}
29. Nd3 Rg6 30. Nc1 Nxc1 31. Rxc1 Qf8 32. b4 Qg7 33. Ra2 Rg4 34. Qd2 Nxg3 35.
fxg3 Rxg3 36. Qf4 Rg8 37. Rcc2 Rg4 38. Qe3 Qh7 39. Rf2 Qb1+ 40. Qe1 Qg6 41. Nh2
Rh4 42. Rf3 Qh5 43. Rg3 Rf8 44. Bf3 Qh7 45. Rag2 Rh8 46. Rg7 Qf5 47. Rg8+ Kc7
48. Rxh8 Rxh8 49. Qd1 Qf4 50. Qd2 Qf5 51. Bd1 Be8 52. Bc2 Qh3 53. Qe1 Qh6 54.
Qg3 b6 55. Qe1 Qf4 56. Bd1 Rh3 57. Nf3 Rxf3 58. Bxf3 Qxf3 59. Rg8 Kd7 60. Rg3
Qf4 61. Kg2 Qf5 {1/2-1/2 The game is a draw.} 1/2-1/2

