{[#]} 57. Ne1 $1 {[%cal Ge1d3,Gd3c5] A very strong maneuver. The knight is
heading for the key c5-square.} Kc6 58. Nd3 Kd7 59. Nc5+ Ke7 60. Kd2 $1 {
[%cal Gd2c2,Gc2b2] The e6-pawn is not enough for to win the game. Therefore,
White wants to create a queenside weakness. The king is heading to b2 in order
to prepare the advance a2-a3.} Bc6 61. Kc2 Bd7 62. Kb2 Bc8 63. a3 {White is
alredy winning. The invasion of the king is unstoppable.} bxa3+ 64. Kxa3 Kf7
65. Ka4 Kg6 66. Kxa5 Kh5 67. Kb6 Kg4 68. Kc7 {Black resigned in the game
Efimenko,Z - Glek,I, 2005.} *

